      "text": [
        " أَبُو جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"مَنْ أَقْرَضَ قَرْضاً إِلَى مَيْسَرَةٍ كَانَ مَالُهُ فِي زَكَاةٍ وَ كَانَ هُوَ فِي صَلاَةٍ مِنَ اَلْمَلاَئِكَةِ عَلَيْهِ حَتَّى يَقْبِضَهُ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3708 - Abu Ja'far Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) said:\n\"Whoever gives a loan until ease of repayment, his wealth will be considered in Zakat, and the angels will continue praying for him until he receives it back.\""
        ]
      }
    },
